author: Brett Davis
title: Mercedes-Benz joining Aussie V8 Supercars in 2013 - PerformanceDrive
text:
In a surprise move it has been announced that Mercedes-Benz will be joining the V8 Supercars race series as of the 2013 season. The move comes after Nissan announced earlier this year that it would provide a mix to usual Holden-Ford-only field from next year as well.
(Image of current C-Class Coupe DTM German touring car shown)
The team won’t be an official Mercedes-Benz partner per se, instead, it will be an alliance between Erebus Motorsport and Stone Brothers Racing. Erebus Motorsport has been running the SLS GT in the Australia GT Championship for the past two years.
The Mercedes-Benz V8 Supercar will adopt the Car of the Future platform (COTF), and it will wear an E-Class-style body. Up to three vehicles wearing the three-pointed star will run in the series, with power coming from an AMG-tuned 5.0-litre V8 engine in specification to V8 Supercars regulations. Power is restricted to around 450kW.
New manufacturers joining the V8 Supercars series has been made possible thanks to new regulations which will come in for the 2013 season, and onwards. The most notable of changes is with the introduction of the COTF platform which has reduced the costs of running in the championship for all teams.
Next year’s season is certainly anticipated to be an exciting one, with four different manufacturers, and four different sets of fans supporting the sport.

author: James Powel
title: Wendy's: One-cent Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger offer is limited per customer
text: Bacon bits: Wendy's confirms one cent Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger offer has limit [James Powel](https://www.usatoday.com/staff/12244761002/james-powel/) [Mary Walrath-Holdridge](https://www.usatoday.com/staff/12093029002/mary-walrathholdridge/) There's only so much bacon that can be brought home. Wendy's is offering a 1-cent Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger in celebration of [National Bacon Day](https://www.nationaldaycalendar.com/national-day/bacon-day-december-30) on December 30. The promotion [launched Wednesday](/story/money/food/2023/12/27/wendys-1-cent-burger-deal/72037785007/) and requires that customers order the penny burger through the company's app or website. A company spokesperson confirmed that the offer is valid for one Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger per customer during the promotion. The deal is an opportunity for customers to relax their wallets after the [holiday spending season](/story/money/2023/11/22/consumer-spending-slows-holidays-inflation/71659583007/). Here's how to claim your 1-cent Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger. When can you get a Wendy's Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger for a penny Wendy's bacon day deal is available between Dec. 27 and Jan. 2 at participating locations. Customers can get one Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger for just 1¢, complete with all the fixings: A beefy patty, applewood smoked bacon, American cheese, lettuce, tomato, and mayo. How to get a Wendy's Jr. Bacon Cheeseburger for one penny Download the Wendy's app or visit the company's [website](https://order.wendys.com/rewards-home?lang=en_US), create a rewards account, and click the "Reward Store." Review the current offers in the reward portal, select the one-cent deal and add it to your order. As long as you have a rewards account, the deal will be added to your cart. Deal hunters don't need to delete the app once they have secured their penny burger: Wendy's often has [other deals](/story/money/food/2023/11/09/free-wendys-chicken-nuggets-wednesdays/71514232007/) throughout the year for reward members, including free fries, chicken nuggets and shakes.

author: GlobeNewswire
title: American Lithium Reports Successful Resource Conversion with Significant Increase in Measured Resources at TLC, up 47% to 6.17 Mt contained LCE | The Manila Times
text:
VANCOUVER, British Columbia, Feb. 27, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- American Lithium Corp. ("American Lithium” or the "Company”) (TSX-V:LI | OTCQX:AMLIF | Frankfurt:5LA1) is pleased to announce an updated Mineral Resource Estimate ("MRE”) for the Tonopah Lithium Claims ("TLC”) project, located in the Esmerelda lithium district northwest of Tonopah, Nevada. The updated MRE has successfully converted Indicated Resources to the Measured category, increasing Measured Resources 47% from the previous 2023 MRE at TLC. The resource block model has been further refined, increasing the confidence of the TLC resource. The vast majority of resources used in the 2024 PEA Mine Plan are now within the more reliable Measured Resource footprint.
The updated MRE was completed by Stantec Consulting Services Inc. of Salt Lake City, UT and is based on an additional 44 drill holes drilled since the previously filed January 2023 MRE.
Highlights : (see Table 1 February 2025 TLC MRE & Table 2 Previous January 2023 TLC MRE, below)
Link to: Figure 1 - TLC Project Updated Mineral Resource Block Outline and Drill Hole Location Map (also see below)
Measured Resource - 6.17 Mt Lithium Carbonate Equivalent ("LCE”) (1,365 Mt @ 849 ppm Li); increase of 47% contained LCE versus 2023 MRE Indicated Resource - 2.39 Mt LCE (553 Mt @ 808 ppm Li); decrease of 48% versus 2023 MRE Measured + Indicated Resource - 8.56 Mt LCE (1,918 Mt @ 839 ppm Li); 3% decrease from 2023 MRE Inferred Resource - 1.44 Mt LCE (345 Mt @ 780 ppm Li); 22% decrease from 2023 MRE American Lithium Interim CEO, Alex Tsakumis states : "We are very pleased with the newly established and upgraded Measured Resource footprint at TLC as it not only increases the resource confidence level in the Measured category but also represents the core of the 2024 PEA Mine Plan. Our focus remains on diligently and prudently advancing our projects as we prepare for an anticipated recovery in the battery metals market.”

title: Bangalore Weather: Heavy Rain Alert Today As Southern Karnataka Drenches; Check Routes Likely To Get Waterlogged | Bengaluru News - Times Now
text:
Bengaluru News
Heavy Rain Alert in Bengaluru Today As Southern Karnataka Drenches In Torrential Showers
Bengaluru is set to receive heavy rainfall on 17 July, with the IMD issuing a yellow alert for the city and surrounding districts. Rain is expected to continue throughout the week, with orange alerts for coastal regions and warnings of possible landslides in hilly areas.
Bengaluru Weather Alert: Heavy Rain Likely, IMD Issues Yellow Warning for City and Surrounding Districts
Bengaluru: After a relatively patchy start to the monsoon, Bengaluru is now bracing for heavy showers, as the Indian Meteorological Department (IMD) has issued a yellow alert for the city. According to the 7-day forecast, heavy rainfall is expected on 17 July, followed by consistent light to moderate showers until 22 July.
With many parts of Karnataka still struggling with deficient rain and parched fields, this shift comes as a double-edged sword — offering relief for some and potential disruption for others.
Heavy Rainfall Forecast Today, Warnings Issued Across Karnataka
The IMD has predicted a generally cloudy sky with heavy rainfall on Wednesday (17 July), followed by light rain in the subsequent days. The maximum and minimum temperatures are expected to hover around 30°C and 20°C respectively throughout the week.In addition to Bengaluru, several other districts have also been issued yellow alerts. These include Kodagu, Mysuru, Shivamogga, Chikkamagaluru, Chitradurga, Dharwad, Gadag, Koppal, Belagavi, Vijayapura, Kolar and Chikkaballapur. Residents in these areas have been advised to stay vigilant for sudden downpours and potential localised flooding.
Orange Alert for Coastal Karnataka, Schools Shut in Some Taluks
While most of southern Karnataka will see moderate rain, Udupi and Dakshina Kannada districts have been issued an orange alert for 16 July due to the likelihood of very heavy rainfall. Authorities have declared a holiday for schools and anganwadis in Ullal and Bantwal taluks as a precautionary measure."With the volume of rainfall expected in the next few days, we are taking preventive steps to avoid any safety hazards, especially for children and commuters," local officials said.
Watch Out for Landslides, Avoid Unnecessary Travel: IMD Warns
The IMD has also flagged risks of landslides in the hilly regions of Kodagu and Chikkamagaluru due to persistent rain. Travellers heading to these districts have been advised to avoid long journeys and exercise caution. "Stay indoors unless absolutely necessary. Travel in these areas should be postponed until conditions improve," the weather office advised.What to Expect in Bengaluru This Week
Here's a quick look at the IMD's forecast for Bengaluru:- 17 July: Heavy rain; yellow warning in place
Despite the absence of warnings after 17 July, light showers will persist, potentially affecting daily commuters, especially during peak hours. Authorities have already issued traffic advisories in several parts of the city due to ongoing waterlogging issues.
